social_posts.post_text: Back after my longest break ever 🧘🏼‍♀️
A favorite shoe and dress pairing lately.
They’re designed by @sean_wotherspoon which is why they’re so 🔥. Never thought i’d be so passionate about a hot wheels product, but here we are!
Really hoping that baggy jeans are here to stay and kinda hope they go even baggier towards jnco style.
So excited to have this as part of my collection. 🌸💐

Chunky Dunky debut 🍦🍦🍦My first job in high school was at Ben and Jerry’s, one of my aim screen names in highschool was a play on phish food, and my favorite Ben and Jerry’s flavor is Chunky Monkey, so these shoes have been on the list for a while!

Bunch of random things lately 🎀✨🧁

Pop-up tomorrow at @smallspacesf from 10a-2p. Honestly so excited and having so much fun writing notes about my favorite memories I made in all of my clothes. Come by to shop over 200 pieces from my closet and the usual cute stuff that @smallspacesf has!

First few days in Japan 🌸🌸🌸
1. Finally getting to wear this @carolinaherrera dress i’ve been admiring in my closet for a while (thanks @mack_fitzgerald for convincing me to get it!)

More Japan stuff from Kyoto and a brief stopover in Tokyo!
1 and 2: fushimi inari - we got here at 6am (thanks jet lag) and there were barely any crowds. 
3. Breakfast at @ichikawayacoffee - i loved the egg salad sandwich and i’m not normally an egg salad person! 
4. Drinks at @bar_gen_yamamoto - a must do in Tokyo I think! I don’t love the taste of super strong alcohol, and the drinks are really balanced and nice and all of the juice that’s paired with the drinks is made in front of you. so special. also i’m LARPing as kendall roy’s gf in this outfit which i tried to copy from naomi pierce (the top is the same, pants are close)
5. Pear gin at Gen Yamamoto
6. Tomato cocktail at gen yamamoto
7. Quick selfie 
8. Yuzu snack on the train - inside we’re yuzu gummies. No photo bc i ate them all :)
9. Our lunch at Mizuki in Kyoto of these things were then made into tempura!
10. First of hopefully many defender sightings in Tokyo!
